# Phase 19 — Repo hygiene (GH-18).
# tauri/ui/assets/mascot/character.glb is the 20 MB rigged mascot bundle
# consumed by the Three.js renderer (Phase 13). Routing all .glb files
# through git-lfs keeps the bundle logically in-repo (Tauri build picks
# it up via the same asset path) while keeping fresh clones small.
# Migration on first apply (developer-side, one-time):
#   git lfs install --local
#   git rm --cached tauri/ui/assets/mascot/character.glb
#   git add tauri/ui/assets/mascot/character.glb
#   git commit -m "chore(19): migrate mascot GLB to Git LFS"
# CI clones without git-lfs still work — the LFS pointer file is enough
# for tests that don't load the bundle; .glb consumers (Phase 13 frontend
# tests) install git-lfs in CI before checkout.
*.glb filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.glb !text !filter !merge !diff
*.wav !text !filter !merge !diff
*.npy !text !filter !merge !diff
*.json !text !filter !merge !diff
.gitkeep !text !filter !merge !diff
